Name: Executive Health Solutions

Name: Better Health Company
Overview:
The Better Health Company (formerly MEND Australia) delivers innovative health promoting programs, training and resources. We design and develop interactive solutions for health professionals, communities and workplaces looking to implement healthier lifestyle behaviours, obesity prevention and obesity treatment strategies for children, adults and families.

Our multi-disciplinary approach is underpinned by current clinical guidelines, evidence based recommendations and national guidance. Our team of experts in nutrition, psychology and physical activity, develop cost effective, evidence based solutions for health, community and education professionals. Our services include:

Programs
We develop and deliver a range of healthy lifestyle and weight management programs. Complete with program training and full supporting resource packs, our programs are ready for immediate delivery in your local community or workplace setting.

Training
Our online and face to face training programs provide health and community professionals with engaging and interactive training in areas including healthy lifestyle behaviours, awareness raising, program specific information and skill development. Our training programs are fully accredited and CPD points are awarded upon completion.

Resources
Evidence based healthy lifestyle promoting resources are developed by health professionals and can be used in clinical practice, with families, in community programs or in workplaces. Resources are easily purchased via our online shop at shop.betterhealthcompany.org

Data
Innovative, customisable web based data collection system provides an interactive platform to manage and analyse program results and participant data.

Name: Samudra
Overview:
The word Samudra () is a Sanskrit term which means "Ocean". In Yoga, we often bind a pose, or create a symbolic seal of our intent to move inward. The word for this seal is "Mudra". It is our intent to bind the experience of ocean and body. Our highly experienced teachers aim to give you the tools to learn or develop your Astanga yoga practice, gain or deepen your awareness of the ocean, ride quality waves and nourish yourself with nutritious, wholesome food.

With our foundations firmly grounded in the ancient Astanga yoga practice, we feel it is important to sustain communities of exceptional, healthy and vibrant people. We are therefore devoted to promoting sustainable living. The key to this is consciousness. Everything we practice, teach and provide has a deep environmental ethos, drawing from nature as much as possible and embracing our place within it.

Our purpose-built space in Dunsborough, Western Australia epitomizes this commitment to sustainability. Here in the heart of the beautiful South West region we lead by example. Drop by some time to experience it for yourself: join a yoga class , come surfing and check out our range of organic threads and bio dynamic fresh produce.

Name: Wanngi
Overview: Wanngi is an exciting new Health App for people.  Wanngi enables people to create their own private personal health record.  For the first time consumers can contribute to their own Health Record and upload medical records to  Doctor and Hospital Visits, Allergies, Medication, Pathology tests, Diagnostic Imaging, fitness tracking, Symptom management all in one place.Consumers can also connect their wearables and look at trends in their health and wellness over time. The Wanngi app is designed with people’s privacy and security expectations at its core.  Wanngi will be a view only portal operator in partnership with the Australian Government to provide a view to consumers for their My Health Record.   Our app does not copy record or store any My Health Record data. Wanngi is ideal for people with low bandwidth, storage or issues with network signals.  This is often useful for people in regional areas.Wanngi is the Australian indigenous Djinang language word for “alive, living one, well, or healthy,” which epitomises who we are and what we do. Wanngi is all about getting you back in control and reconnected with your health.Our Vision;>Provides the power of health information into the hands of consumers.Our Principles; >Trusted App with a focus on helping consumers with their health information>Designing and developing Wanngi with people’s privacy and security expectations as core.Our Services;>Providing people with insightful views of their health information

Name: Your Tea

Name: MeasureUp
Location: Level 1/115 Pitt Street, Sydney, NSW 2000, AU
Overview:
MeasureUp is the fastest, safest, way to assess what's "going on" on the inside using the worlds most advanced scanning technology; Dual Energy X-ray Absorptiometry (DEXA). DEXA assesses bone mineral density and the body's soft tissue composition (muscle and fat mass) with 99% accuracy. Using these measurements we can determine your total body fat percentage, changes in regional body composition and even determine your risk of Type 2 Diabetes and heart disease. We also use the results from the DEXA to estimate your resting metabolic rate, which takes the guess work out of losing or gaining weight! Our staff are accredited exercise physiologists dedicated to delivering individual health assessments and customised advice.

MeasureUp has pioneered the use of DEXA for body composition scans in Australia since 2005. Our director, Dr Meerkin, had been using DEXA as a research tool for 13 years before he established Body Composition Australia in 2005 and subsequently MeasureUp in 2010. 

DEXA can accurately benchmark an individual allowing them to track changes in muscle and fat tissue. Some of our clients include, the Wallabies (Australian Rugby Union Squad), Samantha Stosur (Winner 2011 US Women’s Open), Casey Dellacqua (Australian Pro Tennis Player), Cas and Jonesy (Polar Adventurers), NRL Teams (Roosters, Eels, Wests Tigers, Manly and 2012 minor premiers the Bulldogs) and Hugh Jackman (Hollywood star of films such as Wolverine, Australia and The Prestige) just to name a few.

Overview:
Ask The Dentist – Australia is a free online resource designed to break down the financial barriers to accessing dental education for all Australians. Ask The Dentist is here to answer any questions you have about your teeth or oral health.

How to use Ask The Dentist

Ask The Dentist can be used in two ways, you can ask a question via the question page on our website or you can search and read questions and answers in our database. When you ask a question you can request the question to be private or allow Ask The Dentist to share the question on our blog for the benefit of others. All questions asked will be answered by an Australian qualified dentist within 24 hours. The knowledge you gain from Ask The Dentist will enable you to be better informed about your dental health choices and be proactive about your oral health.

Why did Ask The Dentist Begin?

Ask The Dentist – Australia was started as a way to help the many Australians that are currently on a long public health waiting list or cannot afford to seek help from a private dentist. Ask The Dentist – Australia is available to anyone looking for more information about their teeth and oral health. This online resource is free, timely and removes the financial and geographic barriers that prevent many people from visiting a dentist. You can post questions here or if you prefer Ask The Dentist can be found on LinkedIn, Facebook or Google+. We look forward to answering your questions!

Overview:

Its headquarters are in Perth, Western Australia and it has clinics in all states of Australia as well as in New Zealand and Singapore. History

In 1964 Ashley and Martin opened its first hair loss treatment centre in Melbourne, followed by Sydney a year later, Brisbane in 1968, Adelaide in 1970 and Perth in 1972. Ashley and Martin launched the RealGROWTH (medication for hair loss) program in 1995. The company’s first New Zealand clinic was opened in 2003, with Singapore opening in 2011.

Treatments

Ashley and Martin’s RealGROWTH program utilises pharmaceutical compounds that specifically target the hormones affected by the Male Pattern Baldness gene. Female pattern baldness is also treated.

The Real GROWTH program is a combination of specialty cleansing products, prescribed medications, natural supplements, therapeutic treatments and on-going support.

The company uses laser cap treatment to augment other treatment options.

For those not suited to the RealGROWTH program, Ashley and Martin offers hair transplants as an option using a single follicle transfer technique.

A doctor is employed by each Ashley and Martin clinic to prescribe specific treatments and monitor on-going treatment.

As a not-for-profit organisation led by dentists for dentists, our remit is to deliver value to members and we do this in six key ways:Advocacy: The strongest professions are those that are well representedContinuing Professional Development: Providing comprehensive and respected CPD in world class facilitiesNetworking and Connections: Mentorship, events, local divisions and study groupsProfessional and Peer Advice: On dento-legal matters, compliance, practice management, HR, IR, pharmaNews and Filtering: We deliver what dentists need to know, when they need to know itLifestyle and Benefits: It's not all business. We incorporate social events and lifestyle benefitsFor more information, visit www.adansw.com.au/about.

Name: Life Fitness Australia
Overview:
Life Fitness is a global leader in providing people solutions that help them lead active and healthy lives. The Life Fitness family of brands encourages a full spectrum of active lifestyles, ranging from the traditional fitness options provided by Life Fitness, Hammer Strength and Cybex, activity for older adults and those in rehabilitation offered by SCIFIT and healthy work spaces created by InMovement, Life Fitness equipment is distributed in more than 120 countries.

Life Fitness strives to deliver a superior fitness experience with the best customer support. For inquiries that require immediate attention, please contact customer support directly at 1800 689 622.

Name: Women's Health West
Overview:
Women’s Health West (WHW) is a local non-profit committed to improving equity and justice for women in Melbourne's west. We deliver family violence response and health promotion services.

Our health promotion, research and development program plans and implements activities designed to promote women’s health, safety and wellbeing across three key areas – sexual and reproductive health, mental health, and prevention of violence and discrimination.

Our family violence service provides women and children with the range of services they require while in crisis – such as court support, crisis housing and case management – through to services designed to promote healing and recovery, such as women’s and children’s counselling.

We work collaboratively with communities, government and local agencies, and provide secondary consultation for health, community and other service providers.

Name: World Gym Australia
Location: 29 Coombes Dr, Penrith, New South Wales 2750, AU
Overview: Undeniably, World Gym is a gym. Don’t let that word “gym” scare you because we’re redefining that term. World Gym, today’s gym, is a place where ambitious, motivated individuals work to reach their goals and is an intelligent approach to fitness. Here, you will become better at whatever it is you do. We welcome you to World Gym.The iconic World Gym brand was founded in 1976 by Joe Gold during the glory days of “Muscle Beach” in Venice, CA. Joe was one of the original ringleaders of Muscle Beach. In his prime, he toured with Mae West, and was at the heart of the cozy connection that has always existed between the Muscle Beach fitness scene and the celebrity of Hollywood.Joe blazed a trail followed later by the likes of Arnold Schwarzenegger, Lou Ferrigno, and Dave Draper to name just a few – all of whom had significant Hollywood careers and an intimate connection to and love for World Gym. Since that time, World Gym has evolved into an internationally recognized brand that has captured the imagination of people around the globe. Given its storied past, it is no surprise that World Gym is one of the most celebrated fitness brands in the world today.

Name: Kieser Australia
Overview:
The origins of Kieser extend back to 1966 in Switzerland when founder Werner Kieser opened the first Kieser centre.  Werner was a boxer and a wrestler in the early 1950s.  After an unfortunate boxing accident, he began to look into strength training as a way to speed his recovery. During this time, strength and resistance training was virtually unknown and Werner made it his mission to become the voice for this new type of exercise.  Now, over 50 years later, there are over 130 facilities throughout Europe and Kieser is known as the world leader in strength training for health. 

Established in Melbourne in 2006, Kieser Australia is a network of integrated physiotherapy, rehabilitation and strength training centres predicated on Werner’s concept and the core principle of “Strength for Health”.  Kieser is a new and exciting concept in the Australian health sector. 

We believe in unlocking the potential of every active body. Our unique fusion of health science and exercise science, highly qualified staff and world-class equipment make us one of the world leaders in strength and health training.

Name: MS Australia
Overview:
MS Australia has been supporting and helping people with multiple sclerosis (MS) since 1956. Through an extensive network of centres, branches, support groups and health services, MS Australia provides specialist programs to people with MS, their families, carers, friends and health care professionals.

MS Australia informs people with multiple sclerosis how best to achieve as full and healthy a lifestyle as possible while managing the symptoms of MS, raises funds for the provision of services, programs and research, educates the community, and liaises with government and other bodies on MS-related issues.

Name: Diabetes Victoria
Overview:
Since 1953 Diabetes Victoria has been the leading charity and peak consumer body working to reduce the impact of diabetes.

We support, empower and campaign for all Victorians affected by diabetes.

We are committed to minimising the impact of diabetes in the community, helping all people affected by diabetes and contributing to the search for a cure. Our work covers type 1, type 2 and gestational diabetes, as well as programs for people at risk. We also rely heavily on the generosity of our caring community of members and supporters to help fund our diabetes education, awareness activities and research. Our offices are located at in the CBD at Elizabeth Street and Queensberry Street, Campbellfield and Geelong.

Name: Myzone®
Overview: Myzone is the industry’s leading wearable technology solution. Myzone’s wearable products shows and rewards effort when you work out. It displays accurate real-time heart rate, calories, and intensity with five simple color-coded personalized zones. The telemetry can be displayed collectively in group settings such as boxing or cycling classes, or individually direct to your smartphone via the Myzone app. The app allows for engagement, motivation, and communities to flourish. Respected as one of the most `relevant'​ wearable technologies for the fitness industry, Myzone provides valuable data for operators including personal training departments. With built-in challenges, personal goals, gamification and an online social community, users are motivated to sustain physical activity.Myzone’s primary markets are health & fitness clubs, corporate wellness sites, and educational establishments and are already represented in over 6,000 facilities in 65 countries translated into 19 languages and was awarded the Best Overall Wearable at the London 2016 Wearable Technology Show. For more information, visit http://www.myzone.org

Name: SANE Australia
Overview: SANE Australia is a national mental health charity working to support four million Australians affected by complex mental illness including schizophrenia, bipolar, personality disorders, eating disorders, OCD, PTSD and severe depression and anxiety. SANE's work includes mental health awareness, online peer support and information, stigma reduction, specialist helpline support, research and advocacy. It includes the following services:SANE Help Centre | 1800 187 263 Staffed by trained health professionals (10am- 10pm AEST weekdays)SANE Online Forums | saneforums.org A fully moderated online peer support service that brings together the lived experience of individuals, families, friends and carers in a safe, anonymous and supportive environment (24hrs a day, 7 days a week). SANE Website | sane.org Authoritative, high-quality information and resources including factsheets, guides, articles, real-life stories and research.

Name: BioCeuticals

Overview:
BioCeuticals is Australia’s leading provider of nutritional and therapeutic supplements. 
Renowned for manufacturing and delivering high quality integrative medicines to healthcare practitioners, BioCeuticals aims to consistently raise the standards of natural-based therapies.

With quality, innovation and integrity as guiding principles, BioCeuticals is at the forefront of ensuring complementary and alternative medicines (CAMs) become an integral part of the Australian allied healthcare industry.

BioCeuticals has a strong commitment to research, functional formulas and reliable practitioner support. Our supplements are recognised by qualified healthcare practitioners as well as patients; a fact that reflects our reputation as a progressive force in integrative health.

The BioCeuticals practitioner-only brand is proudly owned by Australia’s largest healthcare company, Blackmores Limited.

On 2 July 2012, Blackmores Limited announced its acquisition of the BioCeuticals brand, which was originally founded by the Hall family in 1993. The BioCeuticals range, brand and strategy are complementary to those of Blackmores. There is strong philosophical alignment between both companies.

Blackmores is committed to preserving the practitioner-only range of nutritional and therpeutic medicine, operating the company as a stand-alone business.

Having this perspective on food causes us to make the effort to supply our bodies with the best ingredients, making us feel excellent – both physically and mentally. I was recently researching methods for improving memory and realized that the food we eat plays a big role in this.

Name: Konekt Workcare
Overview: Headquartered in Sydney with over 280 staff and 40 locations across Australia, Konekt Workcare is one of the largest workplace injury management and workplace health solutions providers in Australia. Konekt’s focus is on helping organisations, individuals and government to maximize workforce participation and productivity, and minimize the impact of workplace injury.We help organisations minimise workplace costs, resulting in increased participation, reduced workers compensation premiums and safer workplaces. We assist employers and insurance companies in recruiting the right person physically and psychologically, keeping them safe and well, responding to OHS incidents, returning the individual to the workplace and redeploying if necessary. Konekt's allied health professionals deliver services across a diversity of industries including government, mining, retail, manufacturing, transport, hospitality and labour hire. Australia's largest corporations rely on Konekt's integrated solutions to manage the health of their workforce, improve processes and identify escalating costs or non-compliance in occupational health and safety, risk management and injury management.  Konekt also has significant customers across large government departments and agencies, as well as private employers.

Overview:

ATMS is a multi-disciplinary association representing 33 modalities and more than 12,000 accredited practitioners throughout Australia, equivalent to about 65% of the total natural medicine profession.

ATMS promotes and represents professional practitioners of natural medicine, who are encouraged to pursue the highest ideals of professionalism in their natural medicine practice and education.

For more information, to become a member or to find a practitioner near you visit: www.atms.com.au

We offer a range of supports, services and equipment, including assessments and advice, in-home support, early intervention, physiotherapy, aquatic therapy, occupational therapy, speech pathology, psychology, case management, orthotics and rehabilitation.We have multiple locations across metropolitan and regional South Australia, and one in Broken Hill. Over the past 80+ years, Novita has become a recognised and trusted leader in providing disability services to South Australians. We promote personal development, we bring communities together and we always have fun!

The sense of belonging within the community has been phenomenal and the training is not only simplistic it has brought me to believe and achieve as well as reaching personal goals far beyond my belief which is mind blowing and I cannot wait to follow this exciting journey"- Michelle ForrestIf you are ready and wanting a change of lifestyle and wellbeing  and are driven to be a success running your own company from your portable office please reach out to us

Name: NUNKUWARRIN YUNTI OF SA INC
Overview:
Nunkuwarrin Yunti of South Australia was initiated in the 1960s by the late Mrs Gladys Elphick, who founded the Council of Aboriginal Women of SA, one of the first Aboriginal organisations in South Australia.

First incorporated in 1971, Nunkuwarrin Yunti has evolved from the Aboriginal Cultural Centre, the Aboriginal Community Centre of South Australia, and the Aboriginal Community Recreation and Health Services Centre of South Australia.

Our first health programme was established with the aid of donations, a small amount of government funding and the services of an empathetic and dedicated doctor.

We became known as Nunkuwarrin Yunti of South Australia Inc. in 1994, and in 1998 were named NAIDOC Organisation of the Year in South Australia.

The organisation is community controlled - governed by an all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Board.

'Community control'​ underpins the delivery of culturally appropriate services to Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people by Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.

Nunkuwarrin Yunti has grown from a welfare agency with three employees to a multi-faceted organisation with over 100 staff who delivers a diverse range of health care and community support services and is a registered training organisation.
Our name was adopted from the dialects of the two largest clans in the southern region - Ngarrindjeri and Narungga to represent the community, the services and the spirit in which they are provided.

Nunkuwarrin Yunti means 'Working Together – Doing Right Together'​ and proclaims our belief of one community sharing a united vision for the future.

This simple belief has seen Nunkuwarrin Yunti at the forefront of initiatives to improve the health, life expectancy and lifestyle prospects for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.

We work with the community, our staff and other organisations to improve and expand our service delivery.

Name: Osteopathy Australia
Location: Suite 4, 11 Railway Street, Chatswood, NSW  AU
Overview: Osteopathy Australia is the national peak body representing the interests of osteopaths, osteopathy as a profession and consumer's right to access osteopathic services. Osteopathy Australia is a national organisation and represents osteopaths in every state and territory across Australia and a member of Allied Health Professions Australia and the Osteopathic International Alliance. Founded in 1955 in Victoria, the Australian Osteopathic Association became a national body in 1991, changing its name to Osteopathy Australia in 2014. Professional membership of Osteopathy Australia signifies a standard of professional and ethical behaviour over and above the requirements of registration.  Osteopathy has been practiced for over 100 years in Australia. Our members are truly passionate about their profession and its whole-body health philosophy. As an allied health option for consumers, osteopaths understand how the skeleton, joints, muscles, nerves, circulation, connective tissue and internal organs function as a wholistic unit, and can assess, diagnose and treat patients requiring assistance with health, neuro-musculoskeletal conditions, pain and injury management.  Australian osteopaths are university-trained, government-registered allied health professionals collectively treating over 80,000 Australians every week, contributing over $350 million to the Australian economy. Osteopathy is one of 14 AHPRA registered health professions in Australia. Our core work is liaising with state and federal government, all other statutory bodies regarding professional, educational, legislative and regulatory issues as well as private enterprise. We have close working relationships with the Osteopathy Board of Australia (the national registration board), the Australian and New Zealand Osteopathic Council (the university accreditor and assessor of overseas Osteopaths) and other professional health bodies through our collaborative work with Allied Health Professions Australia.

Name: Helping Hand Aged Care
Overview:
Helping Hand provides residential aged care, home support services, health care and community programs to older people in metropolitan Adelaide and regional South Australia. Our comprehensive range of services reflects our commitment to choice for older people, and our investment in innovative research and partnerships shows our commitment to respond to our clients’ needs in the changing landscape of aged care in Australia. 

Whether our client chooses to remain in their own home or join us in our home environment, we believe that we must understand the client’s point of view and recognise their needs. Our clients and their families are provided with the opportunity to be included in their care, decision-making and planning at every step of the way. 

Helping Hand has gone from strength to strength for over sixty years, and now employs more than 1,200 staff and 600 volunteers, providing services to more than 7,000 clients across the state. Our work has a national influence on strategy for ageing – through direct consultation with the Commonwealth Government, we help shape thinking and policy. Our clients’ needs and their personal freedom drive how we innovate, plan, manage and deliver services – they are our motivation.

We employ a wide range of Allied Health professionals including experienced and accredited Occupational Therapists, Psychologists, Physiotherapists, Exercise Physiologists, Rehabilitation Counsellors, Behaviour Support Practitioners, Speech Pathologists and Registered Nurses who have experience working with complex and high needs clients across all age ranges and disability/injury presentations. A large percentage of our Consultants are culturally and linguistically diverse (32%) with many who also speak other languages including Mandarin, Cantonese and Arabic. ORS proudly employs people with lived experience of disability and with family members with lived experience; and people who identify as LGBTIQA.

Name: Women's Health Victoria

Women living well – healthy, empowered, equal.

Name: Australian Indigenous HealthInfoNet
Location: 2 Bradford Street, Mount Lawley, Western Australia 6050, AU
Overview: Edith Cowan University’s The Australian Indigenous HealthInfoNet is an award winning innovative Internet resource that aims to inform practice and policy in Indigenous health by making research and other knowledge readily accessible. The HealthInfoNet aims to contribute to ‘closing the gap’ in health between Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people and other Australians.Our work in the area of translational research with a population health focus – in which we are a world leader – makes research and other information available in a form that has immediate, practical utility for practitioners and policy-makers in the area of Aboriginal and Torres Strait islander health, enabling them to make decisions based on the best available evidence.  Our web resource makes published, unpublished and specially-developed material about Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander health freely accessible with the aim of enhancing their knowledge and skills. The HealthInfoNet provides regularly updated overviews, reviews and summaries of Indigenous health status. Materials about specific health topics are freely available, along with contextual information (such as relevant policies and strategies, programs and projects) and clearinghouse functions (details of recent literature and health promotion/practice materials in the area, along with lists of key references and downloadable bibliographies).Our core functions are made possible by funding from the Australian Department of Health.

Name: City Clinic
Location: City Clinic on King, 50 King Street, Sydney, NSW 2000, AU
Overview: City Clinic was one of Sydney CBD's most successful sports injury, fitness and health management centres for over 17 years. "Insider Data Theft"​ by unscrupulous long term employee health professionals, a receptionist aided by a competitor destroyed the business. The Lesson: Data today is one of businesses most valuable assets. The employees you trust most will steal it in a heart beat given the opportunity and the incentive to do so. Budget for the best available security and keep your cyber insurance up to date. “Before” agreeing your business and cyber insurance check you are covered for “insider” data theft and the business interruption and financial damage it causes. Constantly review the "actual"​ value of your data assets. And do not expect any assistance from Aus Govt. Authorities including the Privacy Commissioner or Police. Insider data theft in Australia is not covered by any form of legislation that will result in perpetrators being charged. In fact under current legislation the business owner rather than the thief can be heavily fined at the discretion of the privacy commissioner.

Name: That Sugar Movement

Overview: The impact of sugar, to our waistlines and general wellbeing, has been well-reported in media of late.Our own documentary – That Sugar Film, has continued to educate and shift thinking around the dangers of excess added sugar consumption since its release in 2015. Damon Gameau embarks on a unique experiment to document the effects of a high sugar diet on a healthy body, consuming only foods that are commonly perceived as ‘healthy’. Name: AcroYoga International
Overview: AcroYoga elevates the connection between you and others through movement, connection, and play.  Acro in Greek  means high, or elevated. Yoga in Sanskrit commonly translates to notions of union, or joining. The experience of taking flight with AcroYoga instantly dissolves fears and invites practitioners to tap into new and infinite possibilities of communication, trust, and union. By combining acrobatics, yoga, and healing arts, the practice of AcroYoga has built a community of active teachers and practitioners all over the world.AcroYoga International was founded by Jason Nemer and Jenny Sauer-Klein in 2003. They were the first to codify the AcroYoga practice in 2006. Their work culminated into not only manuals, but also cultivated formalized educational paths that have promoted the highest levels of safety, expression, and straight up fun.

Name: The Push-Up Challenge
Overview: 2021 EVENT DATES:  1st June to 25th June The Push-Up Challenge is Australia’s largest mental health and fitness initiative, proudly run by The Push For Better Foundation, a health promotion charity registered with the ACNC.Participants are challenged to complete 3,318 push-ups over 25 days in June 2021, putting the spotlight on the number of suicides in Australia in 2019. Each day, participants learn about mental health as they are challenged to complete a different number of push-ups that relates to a mental health statistic in Australia.  Participants can aim for 25%, 50%,75% or 100% of the push-up target and other exercise alternatives are welcome.The Push-Up Challenge is a unique way to engage your organisation in mental health by:•	Learning about mental health: A different mental health statistic is shared each day;•	Connection:  Encourages team participation using our push-up tracker (phone app);•	Promoting fitness: Push-ups can be done anywhere and anytime;•	Make a difference:  Opportunity to raise funds for mental healthThe event was founded by Perth engineer Nick Hudson, and in just four years has grown from 4 mates to 130,000 people across Australia, pushing for better mental health. Participants came from across all of Australia, from all walks of life, ranging from school children to a 91-year-old great grandmother.The Push-Up Challenge 2020 saw 130,000 Australians complete 121 million push ups collectively in just three weeks, that’s five push ups for each Australian! The three week challenge raised over $5 million for mental health, increasing physical fitness and awareness of mental health and putting the spotlight on the number of suicides in Australia in the last year.We look forward to having your organisation involved.For further information visit www.thepushupchallenge.com.au or reach out to Head of Strategy and Engagement Roxy Pike via LinkedIn.

Our aims are to: - raise awareness about the importance and benefits of promoting good mental health and preventing mental health conditions, and the ways this can be achieved - advocate for greater investment in prevention and for social and public health policies to promote mental health and prevent mental health conditions  - support multi-disciplinary research to better understand the causes of mental health conditions and to trial and evaluate new prevention initiatives  - work with others to translate research evidence into  information resources, programs and services that support individuals, families, organisations and communities to promote good mental health and prevent mental health conditions - partner with individuals and organisations from diverse disciplines and sectors to create a collaborative and comprehensive approach to prevention.OUR VALUES Humour over prideTeamwork over egotistsSolutions over opinionsEclecticism over silosResponsibility over blameJustice over privilege

Name: Danger Sun Overhead
Location: 300 South Pine Rd, Block D, Brendale, Queensland 4500, AU
Overview: Danger Sun Overhead (DSO) is an education program for outdoor industries, corporate work places, schools and sporting clubs, to promote the prevention, awareness, early detection and support of skin cancers, including melanoma. Danger Sun Overhead was founded when, Joanne Crotty lost her husband, Rohan Crotty, to melanoma in July 2009 at the age of 43, leaving her to raise their 4 boys under the age of five. Jo wants to share her story because most melanomas can be prevented if people have access to education and awareness about skin cancer.Rohan was constantly exposed to the sun as part of his work. After his first diagnosis in 2006, at the time an organiser with the CFMEU, he recognised sun safety standards were not being addressed in the outdoor industries. Rohan became associated with the University of Queensland to help UQ research skin cancer in the construction industry. This study brought the awareness to the hazards of sun exposure into the construction industry.After Jo was compensated for Rohan’s loss, due to his workplace not addressing the dangers of sun exposure, Jo founded DSO who now continue with this important work on Rohan’s behalf through the establishment of the Danger Sun Overhead program.Since the formation of Danger Sun Overhead in 2009, the Sun Safety initiative has provided education to over 50,000 workshop attendees in workplaces across Australia. Danger Sun Overhead’s services continue to be in high demand, delivering education workshops in all Australian states and territories.DSO have implemented our vision of educating apprentices in outdoor industries. Taking the DSO program to the apprentices of all outdoor industries enables us to capture the 15-39-year-old age group, which unfortunately, is the demographic group where melanoma is the most common cancer. By educating the younger generation, who will one day be our next Supervisors, Safety Managers and Foremen.

Overview:

•       Speech Pathology, and

W&L’s Aged Care Funding Instrument (ACFI) consultants assist aged care facilities to receive all of the funding they're eligible for in a way that's both risk free and sustainable. Our services include:
•       ACFI Funding Gap Analysis 
•       ACFI Risk Audits ('The Friendly Validators'​)
•       ACFI Appraisal Pack Submission Projects
•       ACFI Complex Health Care Audits
•       ACFI Education
 
W&L's Online Learning allows staff to complete aged and community care training anywhere, anytime, and on any device. Hosted on a Learning Management System (LMS) specifically designed to meet the needs of  aged and community care providers, content includes:
•       Induction modules  
•       Mandatory training
•       Clinical education, and 
•       Australia's largest collection of ACFI training

Why does W&L exist?
 
W&L recognises the difficulty the industry faces in accessing allied health professionals who understand that there is often more than one client whose needs must be met at the same time - the residents of aged care facilities, the facility itself, consumers living at home, and the aged, community, and disability package providers. Many aged care facilities are at risk of not receiving or maintaining all of the ACFI funding they’re eligible for based on the care they’re already providing. Many aged and community care staff have difficultly accessing training with content designed to be put into practice immediately, is cost-effective, and is flexible enough to ensure that all staff can access it.

Name: Family Planning NSW
Overview:
Family Planning NSW is the state’s leading provider of reproductive and sexual health services. We are experts on contraception, pregnancy options, STIs, sexuality and sexual function, menstruation, menopause, common gynaecological and vaginal problems, cervical screening, breast awareness and men’s health. 

We have five fixed clinics in NSW (Ashfield, Fairfield, Penrith, Newcastle and Dubbo) with more 28,000 client visits annually. We also operate Talkline 1300 658 886, a free, confidential information and referral service, connecting our expertise to communities across NSW. 

We provide information and health promotion activities, as well as education and training for doctors, nurses, teachers and other health, education and welfare professionals.

Our services are targeted to marginalised communities, including people from culturally and linguistically diverse and Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander backgrounds, refugees, people with disability, young people, people from rural and remote communities and same sex attracted people. We also work to assist poor and disadvantaged communities in the Asia Pacific region to access comprehensive reproductive and sexual health services. 

We operate a nationally recognised data and evaluation unit as well as the Sydney Centre for Reproductive and Sexual Health Research, and we publish clinical practice handbooks on reproductive and sexual health used by clinicians Australia-wide.

GIANTmicrobes are for anyone with a healthy sense of humor. Overview:

Overall the health of Australians is very good & has had major improvements in health & life expectancy over the 20th century. However, physical activity, lifestyle & nutrition changes over the recent years had led to a situation where chronic illness & obesity are rising rapidly. We are working to reduce & reverse this trend so that everyone has the opportunity to achieve the best possible health & wellbeing. 

As Ballarat’s leading community health service, BCH is proud to be working with our community & our partner agencies to seek solutions which address these complex health problems.

The team of health professionals at BCH works collaboratively to offer a broad range of health services.

Name: Peninsula Hot Springs
Overview: Peninsula Hot Springs is the first natural hot springs and day spa centre in Victoria, just 75 minutes from Melbourne. The inspiration for the project began when Charles visited several hot springs while living in Japan in 1992. This sparked several years of touring and studying of hot springs around the world.In 1997 the two brothers formed a partnership and they bought the 42 acre site on which Peninsula Hot Springs now stands. The Davidson brothers then found an investor, Norm Cleland, and together proceeded to build the Stage One Spa Dreaming Centre facility, which opened in 2005.In December 2009, the second stage Bath House centre opened, vastly increasing the number of bathing experiences on offer. At the end of 2014, after many years dedicated to the foundation and evolution of Peninsula Hot Springs, Richard Davidson and Norm Cleland moved on to pursue new interests. Bharat Mitra and Bhavani Lev owners and founders of Organic India joined Charles Davidson to continue to develop and evolve Peninsula Hot Springs into a world-leader in the spa, wellness and hot springs industries.Future plans include an increase in bathing experiences, the introduction of accommodation, a food bowl and more.Our brand promise is to 'Connect with your pure nature'​Our purpose is to create experiences where people relax in nature and connect with the deep well of their being.Our values are: friendly empathetic and embracing of all, passionate about inspiring and succeeding, sharing our knowledge, creativity and experience, respectful of culture, communities and nature and responsible for all actions and impacts

Post retirement, and following his great success, Rico  wanted to design and deliver a range of  products that would bring the benefits of altitude environments to the masses.  For athletes in any sport, from the elite to amateur (and everything in between), Box Altitude has comfortable, stylish and affordable 'altitude sleep solutions'​ that improve performance.Now, Box Altitude's evolution continues with the introduction of commercial 'simulated altitude'​ solutions for forward-thinking gym & leisure facilities, spin studios, hotels and performance centres.  Offering altitude training enhances the member experience, accelerates training outcomes for individuals, and creates new revenue streams for owners. In addition, stylish 'altitude bedrooms'​ and apartments have been constructed and seamlessly retrofitted in to private residences for individuals looking to get an extra 'edge'​ in all aspects of life. The health benefits of training and/or sleeping  in 'hypoxic'​ (oxygen depleted) environments are now well-documented, but historically these environments have been cost prohibitive to create, and therefore not accessible to the mainstream (only elite athletes). The Award recognised exceptional achievement in primary prevention within the Western Australian community. The campaign has also won a Mental Health Outcome Award (2009), Mental Health Promotion and Mental Illness Prevention category, and been named a finalist in a number of other Awards over the last few years.

Name: Let’sTALK
Overview: The Let’sTALK Program is a proactive approach to helping Families, Schools, Universities and Workplaces improve their well-being and performance through the power of conversation. Let’sTALK provides a structured approach to open conversation to support and empower people through their everyday challenges to ensure they don't escalate to bigger ones such as mental illness and even suicide.Training is provided for staff and senior students to become Let’sTALK Mentors to have the skills and confidence to engage and empower the person towards working through their challenges with the help of others as required."Letting everyone talk safely" (Let’s) is the vision of the Let’sTALK Program that encourages people to feel safe in talking about their concerns before they escalate. Each Let’sTalk conversation is guided by the following "TALK" strategies:Tell - when there a concern and ask if help is neededAcknowledge - the concern and the person for talking about itListen - to help the person bring their concern to the surfaceKeep in touch - to support and refer the person to a support service as required.

Name: SOFIHUB
Overview: Sofihub is a digital assisted living solution using Artificial Intelligence (AI) and sensor technology (IoT) to support & assist older adults or people with disabilities to live independently in their own homes. Sofihub observes and learns normal behaviour in the home, then identify abnormal behaviour and raise alerts.  Sofihub is also a personal home assistant delivering greetings, medication reminders and hydration alerts.Messages are delivered automatically to the resident based on their occupancy of the room where Sofihub is located. We call this "Occupancy Based Messaging"​.Imagine being able to send a spoken message to an elderly relative via an app on your phone, knowing that they will receive your message automatically the next time the are in the kitchen.  No pendents or wearables are required for Sofihub to work.Sofihub's AI is 1:1 and processed "onboard"​ rather than in the cloud.Families and Carers are able to manage Sofihub via a web application. Trends, Alerts and general activity can also be viewed in the app.  Sofihub has been developed by Deakin University Software and Technology Innovation Laboratories, Sofihub IP is wholly owned by Unisono Pty Ltd.

The Olive Wellness Institute website is intended to act as a source of credible information relating to the health and wellness, and nutrition benefits of olive products, such as Extra Virgin Olive Oil and products derived from the olive tree. The olive tree is nature’s ancient source of health and wellness – it is naturally rich in goodness. It is one of the oldest known cultivated trees in the world, and in many countries, has been used for various health and wellness purposes since antiquity. Our Mission: To gather and share credible information on the health and wellness, and nutrition benefits of olive products. Our Promise:The Olive Wellness Institute is based on the following guiding principles:-	Evidence-Basedo	The Olive Wellness Institute is strictly committed to delivering evidence-based information utilising the highest standards of research. -	Expertiseo	The Olive Wellness Institute is guided by world class experts in the fields of health and wellness, and nutrition, and information is developed by leading scientists, researchers and health professionals who have research expertise in olives, olive oil and uses in traditional diets. -	Credibilityo	All information developed and distributed by the Olive Wellness Institute is subject to extensive peer review as a result of our evidence based, science-first approach

Overview: Esoteric Women’s Health is a global collaboration by women in a wide range of occupations including medical, complementary health and allied health professionals.  All women volunteer their time and expertise and are unified by a common understanding that the current state of women’s health needs addressing.We live in a world where roles and societal expectations dictate largely the perceived worth of a woman. The expectation to be a good mother, daughter, worker or student, lead a successful career, look a certain way, acquire the perfect body, to multi-task, to keep up in the corporate world while juggling family life and so on has meant women have lost sight of the inner-most connection to who they truly are and consequently, have found themselves defined by these roles. At the heart of Esoteric Women’s Health is the knowing that every woman, regardless of age, background, culture, religion or what she has achieved in life, holds an innate quality that is equal in all. It is from this inner quality that she can know herself as worthwhile and from the presence of this quality that we as a society benefit in many essential ways. Esoteric Women's Health holds two foundational understandings when it comes to instigating this necessary change, ensuring it is true and sustainable. ​– That within each and every woman lies the answers to the restoration of her own innate value– That lifestyle choices are key to understanding our state of health and wellbeingThe ability to honour the true beauty and worth that lies within every women and to know that it is from this foundation that supportive lifestyle choices are made and sustained, allows the restoration of a level of health and vitality many have forgotten is even possible. The importance of offering a space to consider how we are currently living and it's impact on our health and wellbeing is central to all Esoteric Women's Health events, services and products

Name: Nature Play WA
Location: Sports Lotteries House, Stephenson Ave, Mt Claremont, Perth, WA 6010, AU
Overview:
About Nature Play WA

Nature Play WA Inc is an incorporated not-for-profit association established to increase the time Western Australian children spend in unstructured play outdoors and in nature. It is founded on the understanding that unstructured play outdoors (nature play) is fundamental to a full and healthy childhood.

Nature play is, of itself, an intrinsic good and from it flow benefits in health, cognitive, social and emotional development and in the building of resilience and creativity. Experience in nature as a child also leads to environmental stewardship later in life.

Nature Play WA is a collaborative organisation working with partner groups to encourage the WA community to value nature play and families to prioritise it in children’s lives. The organisation's primary role is to spread the nature play message and to work to increase access to nature play resources, events and programs.

Nature Play WA began as an initiative of the Western Australian Department of Sport and Recreation and was inspired by the ideas of American social commentator Richard Louv and the Children and Nature Network.

Name: Health Benefits of Good Work (HBGW) Australian Signatories Group
Overview: The Health Benefits of Good Work (HBGW) is an initiative from the Australasian Faculty of Occupational and Environmental Medicine (AFOEM) of The Royal Australasian College of Physicians (RACP). This initiative is based on compelling Australasian and international evidence that good work is beneficial to people’s health and wellbeing and that long term work absence, work disability and unemployment generally have a negative impact on health and wellbeing.The HBGW Stakeholder Executive GroupAFOEM established the HBGW Stakeholder Executive Group in September 2014 to determine the strategic direction for the implementation of the Health Benefits of Good Work into the industry and health sectors to advance AFOEM’s policy in this area.The HBGW Stakeholder Executive Group recommended the establishment of three steering groups to develop and implement coordinated initiatives into both industry and health sectors: the HBGW Signatory Steering Groups (in Australia and in New Zealand) and the HBGW Health Steering Group.The HBGW Australian Signatory Steering GroupIn January 2015, a Signatory Steering Group (HBGW Australian SSG) was established in Australia. The Australian SSG comprises 20 members from a range of stakeholders including statutory authorities, healthcare organisations, re/insurers, national employers and unions. Members were selected following a competitive Expression of Interest process open to all Australian signatories to the Consensus Statement.The purpose of the HBGW Australian SSG is to further champion the integration of the HBGW policy agenda in the industry sector. It has developed into a forum to share information and collaborate on initiatives that will enable organisations to implement HBOW programs as well as champion improvements throughout industry.

Name: SWOX Surf Protection GmbH
Overview:
We believe traveling and exploring the world through surfing is one of the best things in life. Understanding nature, chasing waves and sharing the passion for our sport with our friends and families puts a big smile on our faces and motivates us day by day. This is what we live for. 

We are a group of surfers and snowboarders. Our passion is outdoor sports and we try to enjoy nature as much as possible. If you stay in the outdoors under blue skies and the bright sun for too long, you will face the sun's harming effects on your skin. The problem is: we only have one skin and our skin never forgets - so we have to protect it. 

Traditional sunscreens were never designed for the extreme conditions you experience while surfing the ocean or snowboarding the mountains. Most sun protection products don't absorb properly and might run into your eyes, leaving you with stinging eyes and damaged skin. This can lead to sunburns, premature skin aging, or even more serious diseases like skin cancer or macula degeneration. So we at SWOX got together to create the best possible sun protection products, which fit our needs. And because we know that there is no substitute for expertise and experience, our products are developed in conjunction with both medical researchers from Germany, Switzerland and Australia as well as professional athletes all over the globe. This is the idea of SWOX Surf Protection.

Name: ANZACATA
Overview: The Australian, New Zealand and Asian Creative Arts Therapies Association (ANZACATA) is the peak professional body that represents close to 1000 creative arts therapists in Australia, New Zealand and the Asia/Pacific region. ANZACATA is a member-run self-regulating non-profit company limited by guarantee that seeks to advocate for the profession and to ensure that the training and practice of professional members is in accordance with the highest international standards. It encourages continuing professional development of members by supporting colleges and groups representing special interests and regions, hosting regular conferences and symposia, and publishing a peer reviewed journal: the Australian and New Zealand Journal of Arts Therapy (ANZJAT). Creative arts therapy is still an emerging profession in our member countries, and the association strives to raise its profile, advocating and lobbying for increasing recognition, as well as forging connections and links with other disciplines, and other countries. Our MissionANZACATA recognises the potential of all art forms to enrich and enhance our lives. Our mission is to attend to ethical standards of training and of professional practice, and to advocate for the profession of the creative arts therapies in Australia, New Zealand and the Asia/Pacific region. ANZACATA recognises, acknowledges and respects the ancestors, elders and families of all Indigenous peoples of the lands on which we stand and practice.

Name: Thrive With EFT
Location: 183 Oxford Street, Bondi Junction NSW 2022, Suite 103/First Floor, Bondi Junction, NSW 2022, AU
Overview: We provide mindset change programs  for high performers. If you are driven, ambitious, talented, intelligent, passionate and most of all are clear on where you want to be but feel blocked at times, then we are the right match! You could be excelling in academia, sports, performing arts, career...  Are you content with how you are going? Are you hungry to go that step further, but somehow are stuck? Do you find yourself thinking, no matter how hard you strive, it is not enough? The story of high performers is that although they may be receiving accolades, recognitions and reward for their achievements, there comes a time when they 'feel'​ stuck. The journey to consistent performance is not always plain sailing. In fact the higher you climb, the harder not only making progress, but maintaining progress, can be. We see this in movies and in real life with high performing athletes and wonder why do these champions find their upward trajectories all of a sudden flattening into a a plateau? According to research conducted by Harvard Business Review "high achievers often let anxiety about their performance compromise their progress."​  To aggravate the situation further, they also are at the forefront of criticisms from society quite often.  Being a high performer  comes with its own challenges, expectations, not just for yourself, but others that believe in them too.  In my own personal journey, I have experienced waves of success as well living in shadows of self-doubt. My life long pattern was to continuously strive and drain my energy in doing so. In accomplishing my goals, I sacrificed my health, mental well being and peace in my relationships. My underlying belief was that success comes at a cost. What I have learned is that it does not have to be like that. Now I choose thrive, instead of strive. This is how Thrive With EFT was born.  I have found EFT (Emotional Freedom Technique, aka tapping) a powerful and effective technique that has enabled me to release that compounding stress that I place on myself. EFT is a great enabler in removing the noise we often get blocked, be that noise, a nagging voice inside saying 'you are not good enough'​, or something you have heard from society. EFT helps release negative conditioning, limitations and blocks.   EFT works and its benefits are felt quite rapidly.  My hope for you is to feel empowered, to reach your goals, fulfil your passion, achieve emotional freedom and to find your own thrive, your way!

Name: I'm My Own Boss - iMOB
Overview: iMOB, I’m My Own Boss – A journey of Health, wellbeing, fulfilment and ownership of self, set around a modern day corroboree – A rugby League Football team. The incredible, no unbelievable story of Passion, Dedication and drive of a unique bunch of individuals, Government Organisations,  NGO’s, Private  companies and  Large National Corporations who actually care what happens to our young indigenous kids in the Northern Rivers Community in Goonellabah, Lismore, NSW have come together to support this initiative 7 years in the making. A robust support network have now taken a quantum Leap. 33 Indigenous Girls aged 13 to 18 at the Local Kadina High school have formed a Girls Rugby League team. The ethos behind it is the girls want to take control of their own lives, Health and Well Being. The team, or should I say the extended family unit made up of the weak and the strong, the moderately privileged to the grossly under privileged. The strong take care of the weak and through the next 12 months all the team rise to a united high standard of self-worth were at the beginning there was little to nothing.  A standard that will prepare these kids for life inside and outside the school. The Kids simply wanted to be part of a sports team. Why, “the boys are doing it why can’t we, everything is for the boys”. Team is an interesting word. You can’t be part of a team if you don’t understand the building blocks of a team. The Kadina High School Ethos led by Principal Ian Davies, Dan Matthias the head welfare advisor, Sonya Laverty the newly appointed female welfare advisor and Team leader Mark Ippolito Head English teacher have instilled in these kids the ownership of “Team” and all it encompasses. Ian and his team have handpicked a group of Kadina High school girls, grade 7 to 12, aged 13 to 18, some are born leaders whereas some are lost souls. This program will embrace the lost souls and wrap a security blanket of life experiences around them in a loving caring environment.

Name: InMed Technologies
Overview:
In today’s market a lot of companies make overstated claims supporting their products and services, and far too often these claims turn out to be smoke and mirrors. 

At InMed Technologies, we believe in 3 core principles:

1/. Claims made are based on our expertise of the subject matter - Not an indirect third party;
2/. To truly understand cause and effect, you must conduct the research;
3/. We believe the relationship between the patient and the practitioner is paramount to good health.

These core principles set us apart from all other U.S. companies.

At InMed Technologies we offer specialized products based on our research, hence our specialty in encompassed bacteria and unique delivery systems (see About InMed for more details). We are partly owned by an Australian certified, biologic research and development company, Medlab, who are pioneering several new and novel pharmaceutical therapeutic products (www.medlab.co), giving InMed Technologies access to world-class research and development.

Further, at InMed Technologies we recognize the need to foster strong relationships between the patient and practitioner. To this end, our website strongly encourages a prospective patient to align with a practitioner and purchase through that practitioners virtual dispensary, allowing the practitioner to monitor dosage.

Whilst InMed Technologies is a new company, we are not strangers to the U.S. pharmaceutical and nutraceutical marketplace, previously we have advised, formulated and manufactured for other leading brands.  Our decision to move to a “frontline” position was simple; we believe we can serve the needs of healthcare professionals and patients better than anyone else in the business.

Name: Brain Mind & Memory Institute

Overview:
BMMI is founded by an innovative Australian company Solstice-Mind Matters. The main goal of the Brain Mind & Memory Institute is to support research & development of neurotechnologies both within Australia and internationally. We are dedicated to improving brain diagnostics in clinical practice using qEEG (quantitative electroencephalography) and ERPs (event related potentials) techniques.

Other aims are to contribute to the implementation of neuromodulation and neuroplasticity based modalities into clinical practice. These include non-invasive brain training methods such as  EEG-Neurofeedback or brain-computer interface, transcranial direct current stimulation, computerised cognitive training and others.

 We collaborate with many like-minded national and international organisations, universities and neuroscience laboratories, clinical practices and individual researches and  practitioners.

Name: Active Geelong
Overview: Founded in 2018, Active Geelong is a not-for-profit community of dedicated specialists collaborating to inspire pro-active enjoyment of life, through easy access to physical activity, for everybody, every day.We are a collective impact initiative created to support, coordinate and promote physical activity initiatives in the Geelong region and our vision is for Geelong to be recognised as one of Australia’s leaders in active and healthy communities.Research reveals that 54% of Greater Geelong adults do not meet current physical activity guidelines of participating in at least 30-60 minutes of physical activity on at least 5 days of the week. The impact of this physical inactivity is real, with 10% of premature deaths attributable to physical inactivity.Our goal is to combat these statistics and make Geelong Australia’s most active city by 2029. Geelong is ideally placed to be Australia’s most active city thanks to the environment, weather, infrastructure and access to world leaders in physical activity research.In order to reach this goal, we have identified a number of short-term goals we will need to achieve along the way. By 2022, we want Australia’s most active workplaces and most actively committed GPs to be in Geelong. While, by 2025, we want to ensure every person in Geelong gets their minimum daily dose of activity every day.These long- and short-term goals will be achieved through Active Geelong working with workplaces, local GPs and health professionals and the broader community. Overview: SMART (Self Management And Recovery Training) is a free self-help, mutual-aid program that offers a place for people to in the community to get together and change problematic or addictive behaviours using evidence-based tools and techniques.There are almost 300 free SMART Recovery meetings taking place every week across Australia, each guided by a trained SMART Recovery facilitator. The SMART Recovery program is currently embedded in over 100 Government and Non Government organisations across Australia.During SMART meetings the emphasis is on people’s thinking and behaviour, rather than the substance or addiction, as well as finding practical solutions that are focused on the ‘here and now’.SMART Recovery is underpinned by only evidence-based techniques, such as Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (CBT) and Motivational Interviewing, and to ensure the program adapts with scientific advances, a Research and Advisory Committee of leading Australian addiction and mental health experts was formed.The program was established in the US in 1994, has been operating in Australia for the past ten years. There are now more than 2500 weekly meetings in 18 different countries. SMART Recovery Australia provides professional training courses for individuals and AOD/Mental organisations wanting to learn the program and start new meetings within their community or as part of their organisations service. Name: Australian Commission on Safety and Quality in Health Care
Location: 255 Elizabeth Street, Level 5, Sydney, New South Wales 2000, AU
Overview: The Commission’s role is to lead and coordinate national improvements in the safety and quality of health care. The Commission works in partnership with the Australian Government and state and territory health systems to achieve a sustainable, safe and high-quality health system. In doing so, the Commission also works closely with patients, carers, clinicians, managers, policymakers and healthcare organisations, including those in the private sector.Key functions of the Commission include developing national safety and quality standards, developing clinical care standards to improve the implementation of evidence-based health care, coordinating work in to improve patient outcomes, and providing information, publications and resources about safety and quality.The Commission works in four priority areas:1.	Patient safety2.	Partnering with patients, consumers and communities3.	Quality, cost and value4.	Supporting health professionals to provide care that is informed, supported and organised to deliver safe and high-quality health care.One of the Commission’s key programs is the National Safety and Quality Health Service (NSQHS) Standards, which were developed by the Commission in collaboration with states and territories, clinical experts, patients and carers. The primary aims of the NSQHS Standards are to protect the public from harm and to improve the quality of health service provision. They provide a quality-assurance mechanism that tests whether relevant systems are in place to ensure expected standards of safety and quality are met.The Commission is led by a Board, the members of which are appointed by the Australian Government Minister for Health in consultation with all state and territory health ministers. The Board includes members who have extensive experience and knowledge in the fields of healthcare administration, provision of health services, law, management, primary health care, corporate governance and safety and quality improvement.

Overview: SmileStyler® is Australian made. Name: McKenzie Institute Australia
Location: PO Box 7345, Beaumaris, Melbourne, Vic 3193, AU
Overview:
Developed by Robin McKenzie, The McKenzie Method of Mechanical Diagnosis and Therapy (MDT) is a comprehensive ASSESSMENT, CLASSIFICATION and MANAGEMENT system for people with musculoskeletal problems. The Method is patient focused, evidence based and one of the most rigorously researched approaches in musculoskeletal medicine.

MDT allows patients to be classified into subgroups which assists with differential diagnosis and identifying contraindications to physical therapy. This rapidly identifies patients suitable for exercise or manual therapy and those who aren't; saving time and money for the clinician and patient.

Patient management is based on taking a comprehensive history and interpreting the symptomatic and mechanical response to repeated movements and positions. Management incorporates the latest pain science through personalized EDUCATION and where appropriate, MOVEMENT BASED interventions to enable the patient to SELF MANAGE. Some patients may also require short term 'hands on' therapy and MDT can identify when this is appropriate. 

MDT is taught through a validated and internationally standardised education program. It consists of:

Part A - The Lumbar Spine (28 hours)
Part B - The Cervical & Thoracic Spine (28 hours)
Part C - Advanced Lumbar Spine and Extremities (Lower Limb) (28 hours)
Part D - Advanced Cervical & Thoracic Spine and Extremities (Upper Limb) (28 hours)
International Credentialing Exam (Theory and Practical)
Graduate Diploma in Mechanical Diagnosis and Therapy

Full details on the MDT training program are available at www.mckenzieinstitute.org 

The McKenzie Method of Mechanical Diagnosis and Therapy provides clinicians and patients with the complete ASSESSMENT, CLASSIFICATION and MANAGEMENT framework to enable optimum care.

Name: National Institute of Integrative Medicine - NIIM
Overview:
The National Institute of Integrative Medicine is a Not-For-Profit organisation, which brings together education and research in Integrative Medicine, as well as facilitating its practice at the NIIM Wellness Clinic.

Education
The courses available at NIIM are designed to educate healthcare practitioners in the utilisation, safety and limitations of evidence-based complementary medicine, and its place alongside conventional medicine. For more information regarding post-graduate and other courses at NIIM, please view our Courses homepage.

Awareness
NIIM is dedicated to raising awareness of Integrative Medicine in the community through seminars, lectures, media appearances, news and corporate programs, such as the Complete Health Program. NIIM hosts and sponsors regular public seminars on Complementary and Integrative Medicine. Further information on upcoming seminars and lectures is available on the News homepage.

Research
With the support of local and international partners, the Institute conducts research into Complementary and Integrative Therapies, exploring innovative ideas and assessing the efficacy, toxicity and quality of Complementary and Alternative Medicines to expand the evidence base associated with Integrative Medicine. This research is critical in furthering understanding and utilisation of Integrative Medicine in the medical community.

Representing the multiple specialities in the medical and surgical field, the Consortium aims to create a pan-Asia Pacific “Framework” for the implementation of minimum clinical standards for the screening, diagnosis and management of osteoporosis targeting a broad range of high-risk groups. APCO’s mission is to engage with relevant stakeholders, including healthcare providers, policy makers and the public, to help develop and implement country and region-specific programs for the prevention and treatment of osteoporosis, and its complication of fragility fractures, in Asia Pacific.APCO’s vision of moving towards reducing the burden of osteoporosis and fragility fractures in the Asia Pacific region will be achieved by: o	Securing stakeholder acceptance of osteoporosis as a key public health priority;o	Creating solutions to minimise the burden of osteoporosis and reduce fragility fractures; ando	Enabling healthier ageing through fewer fractures.The APCO Framework will propose clear and concise standards of care involving the screening, diagnosis and management of osteoporosis. These standards will be incorporated into new, or updated national guidelines, and provide a benchmark for the provision of quality care across Asia Pacific. Website coming soon...

Overview:
At Physiotherapy ACTIVE, our qualified team diagnoses and treats a broad range of chronic and acute conditions. We aim to recognise and treat the source of your injury as well as the pain that stems from it, through the use of evidence-based and clinically-proven manual therapy and exercise.
 
Our treatment consists of a comprehensive one-on-one assessment. We will then diagnose the source of your injury and proceed to treat it with hands-on techniques. We will also educate you on why your injury has occurred and most importantly, identify risk factors associated with your injury and use this to educate you on how to prevent your injury from reoccurring in the future.
 
We have a strong focus on self-management. We use a combination of manual therapy and self-maintenance to facilitate your full recovery. Our physiotherapists will provide you with individualised home exercises in order to reinforce the hands-on treatment performed by our therapists, in order to help you achieve full rehabilitation.
 
Physiotherapy ACTIVE also has a fully equipped Pilates studio, where we offer Physio-led Clinical Pilates. This is a great adjunct to your treatment as it helps to prevent ongoing pain and injury.
 
Physiotherapy ACTIVE aims to enhance your full physical health and well-being.

Name: SuperFeast
Location: 20 Brigantine St, Byron Bay, New South Wales 2481, AU
Overview: We really love tonic herbs and medicinal mushrooms. We take them every day. We think they’re awesome. We fell in love with them, they transformed us and we decided we needed to share them with the world. We only want to work with the best herbs. The herbs that are potent, rooted in history and lore, grown with their feet in the soil and the sun on their faces. We want our mushrooms to experience their potential as the connectors and unifiers of the forest before we ingest them, so we can take on those qualities too. You are what you eat.We want our herbs to push up through rocky soil and to compete, to fight to survive, to grow strong. We want to take on those qualities, too. We want to support industries that have been operating for thousands of years, cultivating and ingesting these herbs. We believe in nature. We believe she provides the best feast. We believe we all have the potential to be a little bit superhuman.We only sell what we take. It’s all the same. What we give to our families. And our friends. And to you. Just wild or wild-crafted herbs, extracted consciously, packed with love and delivered to your fave health food store or doorstep ;)The Practical StuffWe sell powdered extracts of tonic herbs and medicinal mushrooms (which are technically tonic herbs but this seems to confuse everyone, so we’ll keep ‘em separated for clarity). What is a ‘powdered extract,’ you ask? Great question. A powdered extract is basically the end result of taking a bunch of herbs and boiling and/or tincturing them for a while. The powder comes about after the resultant extract is dried and pushed through an ultra-fine sieve. Our extracts are 10:1, which means it takes 10kgs of herb to make 1kg of our extracts.
